<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-661-414  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 661 414.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  June 28 1990 v35 n13A p111(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Engineer's guide to getting ahead in telecom: keep abreast ofemerging protocols and standards, say engineering managers.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stenzler-Centonze, Marjorie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Engineering managers offer several suggestions for engineers whowant to get ahead in the rapidly growing telecommunicationsindustry.andP;  The increasing complexity of telecommunicationsproducts requires concomitant knowledge and skills to design,manufacture and support the products.andP;  Recommendations includecontinuing education and even pursuing advanced degrees, keepingcurrent with emerging standards and protocols, work on projectsthat are pursuing leading-edge technology, get a variety of designexperience, acquire knowledge of both software and hardware, bewilling to move into a new speciality, improve project managementskills, expand knowledge of business and financial issues, andremain visible.andP;  Each of these suggestions is expanded upon.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Engineering EducationGoals and ObjectivesRequirements AnalysisTutorialMethodsEmployment Opportunity.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Tips for getting ahead in telecom. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>